SUMMARY:[RICHMOND HILL] Hike @ Wilcox Lake (6km) + Mindfulness & Gratitude
  🙏 
DESCRIPTION:GTA Hiking & Stuff\nJoin us for a Gratitude walk/hike to Wilco
 x Lake in Richmond Hill.\n\nThe theme for this week's hike is: GRATITUDE. 
 We will have some moments of reflecting and sharing (only if you are comfo
 rtable).\n\nThere will also be YOGA for beginners to warmup and cool down.
  I will guide you through a beginner-friendly yoga sequence before the hik
 e and again at the end of the hike. So if you normally leave hikes feeling
  stiff and sore\, this session will be a treat for your joints and stiff m
 uscles.\n\nCome meet new friends while doing a fun and social hike!\n\nThi
 s hike is rated easy and a relaxed pace. Perfect for those looking to soci
 alize while getting in some exercise and suitable for beginners. So\, for 
 those who are looking for short and easy hikes\, you better come out for t
 his one! Only 6km with the option of extending. 😀\n\nMINDFULNESS MEDITA
 TION & FOREST BATHING:\nDuring the hike\, we will practise mindful meditat
 ion and mindful forest bathing (still\, quiet time in the forest). After a
  long work week\, this is a great way to help with stress release.\n\nWe w
 ill find a spot in the forest to practice a minimum of 10 minutes of silen
 t meditation.\n\nHere is what to expect:\n\n* 6km hike to a very pretty Wi
 lcox lake and park\n* Forested paths with flat trails (55m elevation gain)
 \, suitable for beginners\n* Yoga stretches at the beginning and end of th
 e hike\n\n* Gratitude reflection and session for sharing\n* 10-mins mindfu
 l meditation 🧘‍♀️\n* Relaxed pace (we are NOT a fast hiking group
 ). We wait for everyone and slow down when needed/stop and take breaks as 
 needed.\n* Free parking (large lot)\n* Community centre washrooms on route
 \n\nWhat you need to bring:\n\n* wear running shoes\, sneakers or hiking s
 hoes. You can probably hike in good walking sandals\, too.\n* pack some wa
 ter or beverage\n* a sweater for cooler weather\n\nBe prepared for all con
 ditions on trail including mud.\n\nMEETING SPOT:\n\nFREE parking:\nBond La
 ke Public School\n245 Old Colony Road\, Richmond Hill\n\nMEETING TIME:\nPl
 ease aim to arrive by 2pm.\n\nThe session is led by a certified personal t
 rainer and fitness instructor.\n\n***Hike leaves promptly at 2:10PM***\n\n
 \\*\\*\\*YOU MUST UPDATE YOUR RSVP to *NOT Going* if you can not attend. I
 f your RSVP remains going and you do not attend\, you will be marked as a 
 *no show*. You will not be added to future hikes with 3 no-shows.\n\nSee y
 ou on the trail! 👣\n\nChristine Salib\, M.Ed\nCertified Personal Traine
 r Specialist and Fitness Instructor Specialist\, PTS\, FIS\, MBS\, NWS\n\n
 **LEGAL DISCLAIMER AND LIABILITY INFORMATION:**\n\nBy RSVP'ing and paying 
 the event fee (if applicable)\, you are confirming that you have read\, un
 derstand and accept the following:\n\n1. GTA Hiking Meetup is a private gr
 oup. Attending events is voluntary by you as a member. Participation in an
 y activity with us is at your own risk.\n2. By joining this event as a mem
 ber you agree to indemnify and hold harmless its organizers\, co-organizer
 s\, assistant organizers\, event hosts\, and other members from all claims
  or liability of every type (including court costs and legal fees) for inj
 ury or death to any person or for damage to property\, loss of personal pr
 operty or any other wrongful act arising out of or relating to your partic
 ipation as a member. This agreement applies to you and to other persons (a
 s your guests) who may accompany you in these endeavors.\n3. You also agre
 e to hold the organizers as well as other group members harmless. By parti
 cipating voluntarily in the group\, you expressly waive any and all such c
 laims against each and every other member in the group\, including without
  limitation any and all claims against the group organizer\, co-organizers
 \, assistant organizers\, and event hosts.
