SUMMARY:Moonlight Hike - Ajax Waterfront
DESCRIPTION:GTA Hiking & Stuff\nWe will walk at a moderate pace for 4-5 km
 s in 2 hrs or less. Please bring a headlamp or flashlight. The plan will b
 e to walk the paved pathway west towards Pickering. If its not too windy\,
  we will walk back along the shoreline and take in the moon as it rises ab
 ove Lake Ontario. As of now the forecast is calling for a clear night but 
 that can change. The full moon is on Wednesday night so let's hope it will
  be a clear. This is the first moonlight hike this spring. If you haven't 
 experienced a night hike\, come out and enjoy the adventure. Just don't be
  the last in line.😬\n\n**Note**\n- Arrive on time! Don't let the group 
 wait for you.\n- Know your limits! Choose the hike that matches your fitne
 ss level.\n- Dress for the conditions.\n- Free Parking\n- No Dogs\n- The h
 ike will be canceled if the weather doesn't cooperate.\n\n**LEGAL DISCLAIM
 ER AND LIABILITY INFORMATION:**\n\nBy RSVP'ing and paying the event fee (i
 f applicable)\, you are confirming that you have read\, understand and acc
 ept the following:\n\n1. GTA Hiking Meetup is a private group. Attending e
 vents is voluntary by you as a member. Participation in any activity with 
 us is at your own risk.\n2. By joining this event as a member you agree to
  indemnify and hold harmless its organizers\, co-organizers\, assistant or
 ganizers\, event hosts\, and other members from all claims or liability of
  every type (including court costs and legal fees) for injury or death to 
 any person or for damage to property\, loss of personal property or any ot
 her wrongful act arising out of or relating to your participation as a mem
 ber. This agreement applies to you and to other persons (as your guests) w
 ho may accompany you in these endeavors.\n3. You also agree to hold the or
 ganizers as well as other group members harmless. By participating volunta
 rily in the group\, you expressly waive any and all such claims against ea
 ch and every other member in the group\, including without limitation any 
 and all claims against the group organizer\, co-organizers\, assistant org
 anizers\, and event hosts.
